# Quality Checklist

Every completed task must satisfy the following criteria.

## Architecture

- Consistent
- Modular
- Extensible

## Code

- Readable
- Maintainable
- DRY
- KISS
- SOLID

## Security

- Validate input
- Prevent vulnerabilities
- Protect sensitive data

## Performance

- Avoid unnecessary work
- Minimize allocations
- Optimize expensive operations

## Reliability

- Handle errors gracefully
- Avoid hidden failures
- Log meaningful information

## Testing

Changes should be testable.

Prefer deterministic behavior.

## Documentation

Document architectural decisions when appropriate.

Explain non-obvious implementations.

## Final Validation

Before finishing verify:

- No duplicated logic
- No unnecessary abstractions
- No dead code
- No broken architecture
- No hidden side effects